content.detailedDescription:
Outside walking a co worker to her car. a person in the parking lot was looking up and pointed out an object very high in the sky. the round object hovered very high not moving for about 8-10 minutes. i got strangely excited and ran inside to the roof. brought a co worker to see and it was still there. so i ran back downstairs to get a camera. after running back up to the roof it was gone (or so i thought). i walked back downstairs to the other witnesses. they were still looking up and said it moved very fast gong east and suddenly stopped again. they pointed it out to me again and i spotted it farther east but it wasn't moving. had the vallets keep an eye out on it but it was gone after talking to them.

i have always been a skeptic but i cant figure out what the hell that was. felt a need to document it and found this site. good luck.
content.summary: Round white almost shiny

content.detailedDescription:
My father and i were driving down nameless road towards the intersection with rm-1431, between leander and lago vista, on our way to put the boat into lake travis.  it was a beautiful clear day, barely a cloud in the sky.  

i looked out the window and could see a fairly high-altitude object that was reflecting sunlight like a metallic craft would.  it was far enough away that i couldn't be 100% positive as to the shape, but it appeared to be fairly circular, with maybe a slightly ovular shape to it.  it appeared to be moving away, at approximately a 45-50 degree angle from the ground.  i got my dad's attention and told him to look through the windshield to see if it was possible for him to see it.  as soon as i got his attention, i looked back out the window and could not find the object again.  he didn't see it, this time.  i am fairly convinced that what i saw could not have been an airplane, helicopter, or any other craft that i'm aware of.  it was clearly metallic, and had some sort of circular/oval shape to it.  my feeling during and immediately after this sighting was that it seemed very similar to "flying saucers" that people have reported for years, although i had never seen anything like it before.  it was, by definition, a ufo.     

a few hours later we were on the boat out on lake travis, cruising in the boat at about 25mph.  my father was piloting the boat, i was laying out on the back wraparound seat.  i looked up into the sky toward the approximate direction of the road that had taken us to the lake, and there it was again.  i am 95% sure that i saw the same thing (craft) that i had observed a few hours earlier from the truck.  this time my dad saw it too.  i got a much longer look at it, maybe a minute and a half of direct observation this time.  just like before, the metallic object seemed to move away, get a bit smaller, and then disappear completely from sight.  he did not get nearly as good or as long a look at it as i did, nor are his eyes as good as mine.  i was wishing very badly that we had binoculars or a camera with a massive zoom lens to see the craft better.  

also of note- we observed another craft perhaps an hour or 2 later while headed back to the boat launch, but neither of us could eliminate the possibility that this was an airplane at very high altitude.  at no time during any of these 3 sightings did either of us hear a jet engine, prop engine, or a helicopter.  in fact we heard nothing from any of the craft.
content.summary: Metallic object, strange movement patterns and disappearance sighted near lago vista tx

content.detailedDescription: While observing a strange strobe type light in the sky what at first seemed to be a high alt jet with only one strobe visible i was not sure if it was perhaps a ufo because it did not seem to be on a course and first went from east to west then west to east.  also it had no such required lights visible..While i was watching this light suddely a large ball of light like a fire ball appeared out of no where not moving at all and within ten or so seconds faded away.. i was totally shocked and called my wife just inside to get out here to see this amazing sight with me. by the time she arrived it was gone.. next while looking at the sky for more signs she said there it is to the west. this wa only five minutes or so after the first event. tis time the ball appeared out of no where and splt into four equal sized balls all glowing like fire and just as abruptly faded away.. this was repeated again after about five min in a complete different sector of the sky.. we  never saw any after that. this all took place in the sky roughly over an area west of bangs tx around 8 pm or thereabouts. the sky was perfectly clear. whithin 45 min two f 16 air force  planes made a hi fly by.. this is a fighter training area for carswell a f b in fort worth. they may have been sent to see wat was going on. assuming some one else had also seen and called a report in.. this is not very far from the area in stephenville tat made so much news a couple years ago.I had realized the stbe light had some connection with the appearence of these balls of light. comletely different story a few years ago i and another man observed at close range a huge huge triangle shaped object at a low and slow  near hudso oaks tx. i have never reported this.
content.summary: Tiny white strobe evolving into multiple fireballs. connected together.

content.detailedDescription: About 9:00 pm southeast of breckenridge, tx i saw one light that was stationary that would be dim then suddenly glow bright white.  the light was not moving because i was keeping the light lined up with a group of trees.  suddenly, at 9:20 pm a triangle appeared glowing white bright lights and just as sudden, disappeared.....
content.summary: Saw bright lights in shape of triangle southeast of breckenridge, tx on 05-04-10

content.detailedDescription:
We were with four of my friends visiting some of the national parks in colombia called "ca������n del chicamocha", the second largest canyon in the world, after colorado's of course.

we split into couples and walk different paths of the rally, then i found the best spot to take an automatic picture with mi girlfriend with the canyon as a background.

i set the camera on auto, and it shot.

when i was at home checking the printed results of my trip and the events on the holiday, i was surprised when i found something unusual on the picture my girlfriend and i took on the canyon, there was a metal oval shaped objet very far from us (about 6 to 10 miles), right above the canyon, an object didn't notice when we was there.

i say metallic because there's a silver shine on the upper side of the ufo.

is amazing the speed it should have, because i've taken pictures of moving objets before, like aircrafts or cars, even race cars (over 300 km/h or 180 mph) and it've never been 'misty' like this one.

i hope you can give me some answers, 'cause at the moment no one can.
content.summary: I took a picture, and when i was reviewing the images, i found it.

content.detailedDescription:
Was taking out the organic trash a couple weeks ago at work,it was dark and the sky was clear.
on the way back to the store from the organics dumpster i was looking at the stars which i normaly do.
anyway,as i was looking up i saw two dull white lights side by side traveling a little faster than an aircraft.
thought it was an airplane at first but there was'nt any engine noise and i thought to myself that aircraft have colored lights.The two lights seemed to be fairly close together.
just as i hollered at my co-worker to look at the lights they separated from eachother at a 90 degree angle from their travel.
they went quite a distance from eachother then just disapeared.
they were'nt like any falling stars i have ever seen and were'nt as bright.
my co-worker said it was a falling star or a satellite falling, even though he didnt see it.
i've never seen falling stars travel side by side and seperate like these lights did.
content.summary: 2 dull white lights travel together then separate

content.detailedDescription: I was about to go up the stairs to my apartment when a blue light through the tree about 100 feet away caught my eye. i focused on it abd saw that there were four royal blue lights. three in triangle shape with one in the middle. i tried to get a clear look at it but it seemed to try to stay out of my direct line of sight. i ran down a hallway under my apartment to get a better look and wasnt able to see it again. from the moment i saw it to right know i still have this feeling that i have to see it. i will be watching all night.
content.summary: There were 4 royal blue lights going back and forth changing directions behind a tree.

content.detailedDescription:
I too have noticed this star like object several times in the past and have photographed it with a canon eos10d on a tripod back in early 2009 but have never reported it because i pointed it out to a few people and got the typical response... well you know. 

so after seeing the report from pa i thought i would just put it out there to see what happens.

i too was seeing the red, blue, and green colors and was photographing it in a high speed sequence when i noticed it seemed to have a repeating pattern to it. then something really bizzare happend, it blinked off for a split second then started over again. 

i put together a short video comprised of several still photo's in the natural order they occoured from that night and it runs in about 1/4 real time. in addition the last 2 photos are of the object when it appeared to blink off but the camera caught something very strange looking that i couldn't see with the naked eye.

i remember thinking to myself at the time, silly seti; don't you think an advanced civilization would communicate using something like light and primary colors other than radio waves?
content.summary: Follow up to "star like object changing colors to blue, green and red" in pa.

content.detailedDescription: I was watching the sky in my yard and i started to notice many faint star like lights that did not appear to blink travel very quickly across the sky. they all moved in different directions and at one point 3 of them got so close to each other that they nearly crossed paths. this is the second time i have seen these objects in the sky, however there were many more this time. what i found amazing was that right before i would see one, i would have a strong feeling that it was coming, almost sensing its presence.
content.summary: Multiple star like ufos

content.detailedDescription: I watched a bright white light travelling silently west to east for roughly ten seconds, the light then went out.  i videoed this & have attached still shots taken from the video.
content.summary: Large bright light

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend and i were sitting in the back yard, facing east.  i noticed many white birds loitering at about 500-1000 ft.  she looked for a second, then pointed out a 'white dot' that seemed motionless.  i spotted it, and after about a minute it began moving slowly, taking an irregular path to the south. after another minute or two it stopped moving.  after another 20-30 seconds the object moved again.  slowly, as before, but this time in more of an eastward direction.  i watched for another 30-60 seconds, then i went inside the house to look for my binoculars, as the object was too far away to see any detail.  when i emerged from the house, the object was gone.
my girlfriend and daughter (10 yrs old) witnessed the object.
content.summary: White dot

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving with a friend of mine (who also witnessed it) in lawrence, ks, driving west on 6th street, just west of downtown lawrence, when we noticed a really strange object up in the sky.  it was about the altitude that a helicopter would fly, but it wasn't a helicopter.  it was located north and west of where we were.  it was the middle of the day.  i guess we noticed it because it was there, up in front of us, easy to see.  

it really mystified me because although it wasn't an airplane or a helicopter or a balloon, it also wasn't a disc, which is what i always thought, based on a past experience, a ufo would look like.  this thing was metallic but tall and sort of shapeless.  it was multi-faceted.  it didn't seem to be flying, but hovered where it was.  i don't know what shape to call it.  i guess it was closest to a cylinder, but it wasn't smooth.  it seemed multi faceted.  i didn't know what it was.  i still don't.  it was confusing.  we watched for as long as we could, given the traffic, and wondered out loud what the heck it was!    

we would have tried to watch longer and investigate it further, but i had to get home to nurse my baby. 

the weird thing about the experience is that i somehow forgot about it until my friend mentioned it a couple of years later.  after she brought it up, it all came back to me.  i have always been very interested in ufos, so it was disturbing to me that my memory of this event would be so fleeting.  

in thinking about where this thing was located, i kind of wonder if it wasn't checking out the coal fired power plant to the north of where we were.
content.summary: Ufo in lawrence, ks, in the middle of the day.  october, 2004.

content.detailedDescription:
On tuesday may 4 2010 between 9:15 pm and 9:30 pm i was looking north from my location when i observed a small aircraft headed east from my 10:oo position approximately 1 or 2 mile away. as the small aircraft hit my 12:00 position directly north of me half mile out with his taxi lights on he begain a 10 degree or so left wing down turn from east to north and shut his taxi light off. 

just after his taxi lights went off, a huge white sphere appeared approximately 300ft directly above the small planes canopy and rapidly shot straight down to within 100ft or less of of small planes canopy before completely disappearing. 

with the size of the sphere being roughly a quarter to half of the size of the small patrol aircraft the pilot seemingly did not notice the event directly overhead. he continued a huge loop and came back around with taxi light on again and following same approach towards my position and once again when he was directly north of me, a giant white sphere appeared at extreme high altitude this time from an easterly direction and shot straight toward the small plane at the perfect angle and dissappeared within 2-3 miles from head on with small plane. the small plane shut his taxi lights off just after the sphere lit up and began to turn.

i thought to myself that this pilot may have missed seeing it the first time but the second time no way. it came straight toward him extremely fast and from up high but was well out in front of him. object appeared to be size of vw or big earthball without the fire and tail just a solid white sphere but hauling butt and still the small plane didnt so much as flinch while turning his taxi lights off!??

it appeared to be like a game of cat and mouse just directly over a populated city and im not sure the mouse was aware.

the small plane appeared to be some type of civil patrol or police plane just bigger than typical cesna single engine type 172. maybe a piper pa 28 or similar. 

night was clear and dry with excellent visibility of stars.
content.summary: White sphere over patrol aircraft

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking out of a friends house and noticed a star-like object in the sky shimmering the colors red, blue, and green. i pointed this out to the two other individual's that were with me and we decided to go to the over-look for a closer look. before heading down we grabbed another individual and the binoculars. looking at the object with the naked eye we could see the colors flashing randomly; through the binoculars the object seemed to remain white in color. the object seemed to move farther away, so we decided to go back to the first place we seen the object. once back at the original spot we lost sight of the object.


this is not the first time that i have seen this type of object over lake erie. between 2008 and now i have seen this occurence more than 10 times.
content.summary: Star like object changing colors to blue, green and red.

content.detailedDescription: Four days ago, i was laying in my lounge chair peering at the sky. i noticed several small dots moving about. i have seen this every night now for the last four days. it is like they are all scrambling to get into position before total nightfall. after the nightly event the airplanes will then start to appear. its like the star sized craft know this. i have seen four to six of these during this event. last night about 9:45 i watched two ufo's crossing each others path at the same altitude.( approx. 15 to 20 miles up) the one that was heading south seemed to signal the one coming from the west with a really bright pulsating light, which made the one ufo a hundred times the original size. the one heading east accelerated as the one heading south seemed to quickly decelerate ( not stopping, just slowed down quickly) this is in total comparison to a horn honk and brake slam in an intersection. in amazement i went out to look again ( as i have for the past several nights} there is nothing in the skys but airplanes. it seems to be scheduled as i have only seen this between 9:15 and 10:30.  this is just east of the little and big dipper. (looking east) if anybody out there peers into the same area and notices this, please feel free to e-mail me. thank you for reading and happy hunting. -robert m peternell
content.summary: Two ufo's intersecting. one ufo pulsated bright light to avoid collision.

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting in a recliner watching tv, as i usually do every evening. over a period of time i've noticed a fairly bright light out our kitchen and dinette windows. this has been most acute in the last week of april into this early week of may. i live in a rural developement sw of the small town of sinking spring. the windows described above face north. these lights were seen by me and my father to our nw. a few days ago, the
unidentified occurance piqued my interest to the point of me geting my binoculars and viewing it. the binoculars are not the most powerful; ie.
7x35mm. i saw a v or triangle shape with lights along both sides, blinking.
the lights were more bright on the left side(as viewed by me). there were 3
of them and 3 less bright flashing on the other side. the object was about 1 inch in width as viewed by my field glasses. i went upstairs to get my dad to witness it, but he did not see the same shape and light array as i.
the other night i saw lights dancing around the same section of sky. this
phenomenon appears every night around 9:24 till about 10:00. once i saw it dip to the right with a red light showing as it fell below my horizon. last night, there was a stationary presence, same place, same time. there was also dancing lights. after the lights seemed to have gone, a helicopter
flew on a sw to ne diagonal line. this would have been between myself and where the object was operating. although i have an interest in ufo's, this is my first and only sighting. it took some courage for me to observe this.
i expect this to happen again tonight.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Night time ufo sighting

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting in my bedroom floor playing a videogame.Must have around 3:30 a.M. i was charging video camera cause i thought my neighbors were snooping around my house. so i just happened to look out front window,and what looked like a huge,huge bright like a full moon was gliding like a loose balloon. it was maybe 50 yards away from window and it looked like it was in back of my neighbors house. must have been size of two house's. so i quickly grabbed the video camera and woke up my wife to show her.And i recorded about 30 seconds cause film in camcorder was at end of tape. this happened about five to six years ago. never thought of reporting itonly because i don't think my photage is that good. but you can see what i recorded. i think i only seen footage maybe twice since i recorded it.I thought maybe a full moon but then i remembered i seen same thing about two nights before that day. so this objesct went from my left to right just gliding slowly and confused the hell out of me. i dont remember if i lost sight of it or not. my wife was mad at me for looking out of window at that time. we just put the blinds back down because i to lift blinds to look outside. after we just laid down and went to sleep. i was kind of scared what if it saw me. me thinking it was a u.F.O. i freaked out so i didn't look out window again.
content.summary: Large moon like

content.detailedDescription:
Erano le 7,00 di mattina e stavo aspettando che aprisse un'ambulatorio per tariffa una visita medica.
ad un tratto spunta da dietro palazzo delle nazioni unite era un'aereo che appena decollato dall'aereoporto cristoforo colombo di genova, lo seguo con lo sguardo fin sul mare, quando la mia attenzione ricade su tempo condensato scope argentato in lontananza si muoveva che si molto lentamente in principio pensavo fosse un'altro aereo in lontananza ma appena si e fermato in cielo allora ho capito che nn poteva un'aereo essere.
l'scope era inizialmente sul mare e si muoveva si molto lentamente verso est fin a si che nn e fermato, e tariffa senza nessun tipo di manovra si e diretto verso nord ovest dirigendosi verso di me, il suo movimentoera molto lento e mentre si avvicinava diventava sermpre piu visibile la sua forma, ovvero cilindrica e di colore argento molto acceso uno tal quale punto mi e venuta la cosidetta pelle d'oca nn mi sembrava neanche vero "sono rimasto senza parole, e quindi era il che nel momento piu vicicino una a me ho scattato foto col cellulare mio, purtroppo essendo sprovvisto di zoom la foto e piccola un po venuta, comunque l'ho seguito scope acora per 1 minuto circa fino a che nn e sparito dietro il palazzo colomba appunto tariffa dovevo la visita.
adesso alleghero 2 foto di una e qulla originale il che ho fatto col mio cellulare invece l'alta e la foto con delle nazioni unite tentativo dingrandimeto eseguito da mio fratello che esegue video di montature per alcune televisive reti ...
detto tempo condensato vi ringrazio e spero di ricevere notizie silla mia foto
grazie in anticipo ...
content.summary: Oggetto apparentemente conico di colore argento

content.detailedDescription: This time...Being my fourth time to witness the lights...I grabbed high power binocs to see actual object...It was airplanes dropping flares...99% sure...Probably as many as 10 planes...I could see planes lights coming on and off at different times .... i guess to keep from colliding with other aircraft...You could just barely see the lights the naked eye...They would come and go...That is how i could see where the next flare or flares would appear...The flares would only last 3 seconds at longest...High altitude and many miles from abilene...Guessing the start of the hill country or so. odd that i could not pick up the red lights on the planes at all...Just the bright white strobe light that would appear at different times...I followed one of the planes that did have lights on breifly and saw the object drop the flares...These are the same lights that i have previously seen.
content.summary: Orange lights seen again south of abilene

content.detailedDescription: Last sunday in march, i was driving down pleasant rd towards carowinds to meet a friend at a target. time was approximately 7:30 pm. pleasant rd has a mix of business locations and neighborhoods. this happened close to an industrial area / business park. spotted a bright silver object in the sky. it looked like it was made of metal. could not hear any sound. there were several tornado warnings at this time and the object was slowly ascending into the storm clouds. appeared to have legs and antennas. bright lights were flashing on both sides of object. object seemed to be several stories up. although there was some moderate lightning in the area, this object caught my eye because of its extremely bright flashing lights. i live 15 minutes away from an airport and this object was well below planes that were coming in for a landing or just leaving the airport. i watched it until it permanently dissapeared into the clouds.
content.summary: During bad storm, spotted a  metallic silver round object with flashing lights.  appeared to have some type of antennas and legs.

content.detailedDescription: Was closing the bedroom blinds and noticed a brilliant light toward the west which was too big and bright to be a star.
content.summary: Horizontal bright lights stationary above the oquirrh mountains. observed for 20 minutes in one spot and then it moved east.

content.detailedDescription:
I am a 47-year old computer consultant living in cheltenham, gloucestershire, in the united kingdom. i have been interested in the subject of ufos ever since i picked up a paperback by donald keyhoe which had been shelved in the science fiction section of a bookstore in the 1970���s! i have never reported a ufo sighting before, nor seen one, except for a possible uav sighting in fog over cheshire oaks retail park (a few miles from the british aerospace plant at warton) a few years ago.

the sighting i am reporting here is more unusual and seems to conform to the ���black triangle��� type of vehicle which is frequently reported in recent years, and may be of interest to people researching the subject.

over recent nights (late april, early may 2010) at home i have noticed an orange light in the western sky after dark, corresponding to the common position of venus and visible when other stars are not (due to street lighting). i should explain that my home is in a high-rise residential block in a town which is almost all low-rise buildings, so i have unobstructed views to the west over the severn valley from the malvern hills to the forest of dean, and south over cheltenham town centre to the nearby cotswold escarpment. i assumed this object was either mars, or venus red-shifted due to the icelandic volcanic dust in the atmosphere. we have certainly enjoyed some very red sunsets recently.

at approximately 1:20am bst (0:20 gmt) on the may bank holiday monday, 3 may 2010, i assumed i was looking at this same object from my kitchen window a few degrees above the horizon to the west when i thought i could perceive it to be a cluster of different coloured lights instead of a single source. i left my kitchen (which faces west) to retrieve a pair of small binoculars (15x21) and returned in time to see the object changing position or aspect. through the binoculars i had difficulty keeping the image still but could distinguish a red strobe light and fixed white lights, with an occasional blue light also visible (possibly strobing or flashing occasionally). the object now appeared to be moving closer and slightly to my left heading for the centre of cheltenham (which is just south of my location).

as it moved it presented itself at an angle to me and i could see the red strobe light was centred on the underside of the object which now clearly had strong white lights at the front, throwing a beam or twin beams straight ahead, like landing lights or car headlights. conditions were clear for visibility but the white beams illuminated moisture in the air immediately in front of the object as it was quite a cold night. the ���wing��� tips on either side of the object appeared to have small fixed white lights like navigation lights, which occasionally also showed blue and i think red lights at the same locations. these lights appeared unusual to me as i would expect a single fixed green (starboard) and red (port) navigation light to be visible on a light aircraft or the police helicopter, both of which are familiar sights in this area. civil aircraft in the uk have a white strobe, so i thought this might be a military aircraft instead.

i moved to another room to observe the object as it passed to the south side of my building over the centre of town and could clearly see the object was a large black triangle or delta shape. the height of the object was level with my apartment (sixth floor) and the top of the cotswolds (1000ft elevation), and about the normal operating height of the police helicopter or lower. the lights observable at this time were the two wing tips or rear corners of the triangle which showed small fixed white lights and possibly a red one on the nearside (port) wing. the red strobe was larger and definitely in the centre underside. the trailing edge appeared to be a straight edge and slim, like the old vulcan bomber and not like the b2 or f117.

i opened the window at this point to see if any sound was being made by the object and could hear a low jet type of sound, receding as the object moved away over the cotswold escarpment to the south-east. the sound level was similar to a wide-body jet going over at high altitude and not what you would expect from a large object at low level and certainly not enough to wake anyone up at this time of night. the object disappeared over the cotswolds heading south east towards oxfordshire and i got the impression it had made a turn over cheltenham at about the time i switched rooms. i checked the time, which was 1:25am bst, so i estimate the duration of the sighting at approximately 5 minutes.

the only military traffic we usually get here are the odd fast jet making a run to the bomb ranges in wales and regular ch47 chinook helicopter flights training pilots for afghanistan. these are always in daytime and the chinooks tend to come from the north and turn west over cheltenham to ���box��� around staverton airport and head back north again. so this sighting was definitely an unusual vehicle.
content.summary: Black triangle over cheltenham, england, unusual nav lights, little sound.

content.detailedDescription: My wife had just walked outside the front door to lock the pickup.  when she saw a green fireball fall straight down from the sky to the south of her.   she said that it was large and very bright and appeared to hit the ground.   no sound was heard.   the sky was clear.  the city light were bright but the green firball was very bright.  i heard her make a loud exclamation, and ran down the stairs to see what was wrong.  she had a reacition of awe.
content.summary: Green fireball comming straight down due south of our house.

content.detailedDescription:
I was attempting to study the chemistry building, in on of the upper floors, through out the night from approximately 12 am onwards.  

at approximately 4:25 am i heard a strange humming sound that i have not heard before.  i found it strange because i have heard these humming sounds before in different areas throughout the neighborhood for a while now.  

at first i thought these sounds was from an air conditioning unit but i wondered why all of a sudden at 4:25 am.  at times it seemed to be farther away for several minutes but then return with the same volume as before.  

at stayed in the room i was in throughout this incident until approximately 5:40 am, which is the time i left the building since the humming sounds seemed farther away again.   

after exiting the building and after approximately a three minute walk i happened to look up and i saw a disk shaped object that wobbled towards me and i saw a flash and it disappeared; it was 5:51 am mst when i saw this.  i then saw another object but at a much higher elevation.  i'm only assuming that it may have been the same object.
content.summary: Ufo on asu campus -- chemistry building

content.detailedDescription: Ok, they're back ..My friend called me on my phone and said quick look outside those lights are back. so i went out there, saw nothing at first after about 5 minutes multiple lights came on. usually they would come on in a row of some sort. this time they came on about 6 of them but staggered, but this time one of the orange lights was actually 3 smaller orange lights grouped into one (if that makes sense). they didn't come back on after that. so if you're in the area please looks the following nights between 9pm-10pm. last time they came back every night for i can't remember now but i think it was 8 or 9 nights in a row.
content.summary: Multiple orange lights

content.detailedDescription: 2 lights at very high altitude. alternating in brightness just appeared. it looked like they were coming straight down, very fast direction change then flew south towards atlanta. the lights were to far apart to be one vehicle. they varied from very intense bright lights to very dim. there were no flashing lights or running lights. i thought at first they were shooting stars. at one time they were as big as erasers.
content.summary: 2 stars approx. 2 miles far apart.
